{"lemma":"شَمْعُ","slug":"شَمْعُ","root":"ش.م.ع","root_slug":"ش-م-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-م-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":9},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n23019","n23022"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%92%D8%B9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wax","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"candles","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a thing one lights, a torch, lantern","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to wax, to rub or smear with wax"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make waterproof or wax-coated"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to play, to sport, to game"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to joke or jest"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be mirthful, to laugh"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to become scattered, to become dispersed"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ش م ع (š m ʕ) meaning \"to spread or disperse\", hence melting wax.\n\nProbably denominal.\n\nFrom the root ش م ع (š m ʕ) in the sense of \"to disperse or go away\", \"to be away from work\", hence \"to be at leisure\"."},"ipa":["/ʃamʕ/","/ʃa.maʕ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n23019","headword_ar":"شَمَعَ","root":"$mE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amoEN","text_ar":"شَمْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$umuwEN","text_ar":"شُمُوعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$omaEapN","text_ar":"مَشْمَعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He played, sported, gamed, jested,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"joked:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was mirthful, and laughed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amaEatN","text_ar":"شَمَعَتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor. as above, inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amoEN","text_ar":"شَمْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$umuwEN","text_ar":"شُمُوعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She cheered by her discourse."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano yat~abiEi Alma$omaEapa ya$omaEi A@ll~`hu bihi","text_ar":"مَنْ يَتَّبِعِ المَشْمَعَةَ يَشْمَعِ ا@للّٰهُ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * O)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He who follows the practice of play,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sport,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unprofitable play"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sport, with men,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and derision and laughter and enjoyment with them, God will requite him for that,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God will cause him to be in a state in which the like shall be done with him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amaEa","text_ar":"شَمَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$umuwEN","text_ar":"شُمُوعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, scattered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dispersed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-'Abbád, O, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K"]},{"entry_id":"n23022","headword_ar":"شَمْعٌ","root":"$mE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amaEN","text_ar":"شَمَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", both chaste accord. to ISd: (TA:) accord. to Fr, (S, O, Msb, TA,) the former is post-classical; (S, O, Msb, K, TA;) but ISd says that this is a mistake: (TA:) accord. to ISk one should say the latter, and not the former: (TA:) or accord. to him, the word is with fet-h to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m","text_ar":"م"},{"kind":"text","text":", and some of the Arabs make the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m","text_ar":"م"},{"kind":"text","text":"quiescent: accord. to Th, it is with fet-h to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m","text_ar":"م"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and if you will, you may make it quiescent: accord. to IF, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m","text_ar":"م"},{"kind":"text","text":"is sometimes with fet-h; so that he gives one to understand that it is more frequently made quiescent: (Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A kind of thing with which one lights himself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muwmN","text_ar":"مُومٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which, or rather"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muwmo","text_ar":"مُومْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in Pers., signifies both"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wax"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wax-candle;"},{"kind":"text","text":"both of which or rather the former and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wax-candles,"},{"kind":"text","text":"are meant by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amoEN","text_ar":"شَمْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amaEN","text_ar":"شَمَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (ISk, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muwm","text_ar":"مُوم"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of honey"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bees' wax"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Lth, K:) the n. un., (CK,) or what denotes a piece, or portion, thereof, (so in copies of the K and in the TA,) is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amoEapN","text_ar":"شَمْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amaEapN","text_ar":"شَمَعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$mEp","text_ar":"شمعة"},{"kind":"text","text":"has a more particular signification. (S, O.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","S","O","Msb","K","ISk","Lth","CK"]}]}}